cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CR 

The paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a framework that involves adversarial learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with binary coding and optimization, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
